no argument there,

00:16:18.500 --> 00:16:21.860
they can sell your reward,
they can sell you immediate gratification,

00:16:21.860 --> 00:16:24.539
I have no problem saying that.

00:16:24.539 --> 00:16:26.860
The question is,
"Are they selling you happiness"?

00:16:26.860 --> 00:16:30.659
And the fact of the matter is
they're actually taking away your happiness.

00:16:30.659 --> 00:16:34.299
So what is the difference between these
two terms, pleasure and happiness?

00:16:34.299 --> 00:16:38.460
Number one, pleasure is short-lived,
happiness is long.

00:16:38.460 --> 00:16:41.740
Two, pleasure is visceral,
you feel it in your body,

00:16:41.740 --> 00:16:46.059
like all of those substances
having those systemic effects.

00:16:46.059 --> 00:16:50.100
Happiness is ethereal,
you feel it above the neck.

00:16:50.100 --> 00:16:53.146
Pleasure is taking,
happiness is giving.

00:16:53.147 --> 00:16:55.340
Pleasure is experienced alone,

00:16:55.340 --> 00:16:57.899
happiness is usually experienced
in social groups.

00:16:57.899 --> 00:16:59.940
Pleasure can be achieved
with substances,

00:16:59.940 --> 00:17:02.779
happiness cannot be achieved
with substances.

00:17:02.779 --> 00:17:06.259
The extremes of pleasure
whether they'd be substances or behaviors...

00:17:06.259 --> 00:17:14.051
So substances like cocaine, alcohol,
nicotine, opioids, heroin, sugar

00:17:14.052 --> 00:17:19.819
or behaviors - shopping, gambling,
Internet, social media, porn.

00:17:19.819 --> 00:17:23.099
In the extreme all lead to addiction.

00:17:23.099 --> 00:17:26.700
There's an "-aholic"
next to every one of those.

00:17:26.700 --> 00:17:31.019
Shopaholic, sexaholic, alcoholic, chocoholic
you know, down the list.

00:17:31.201 --> 00:17:33.081
There's no "happyaholic".

00:17:33.161 --> 00:17:34.859
There's no "happyaholic".

00:17:34.859 --> 00:17:38.099
You can't be overdosed
on too much happiness, don't exist.

00:17:38.099 --> 00:17:43.539
And then finally number seven,
pleasure's dopamine happiness is serotonin.

00:17:43.539 --> 00:17:48.140
Now why do we care?
What does it matter? Here's why.

00:17:48.140 --> 00:17:52.299
Dopamine is an excitatory
neurotransmitter.

00:17:52.299 --> 00:17:55.906
Every time dopamine is released,
it crosses the synapse,

00:17:55.907 --> 00:18:01.819
binds to its receptors on the next neuron,
the neuron fires, it excites the next neuron.

00:18:01.819 --> 00:18:05.339
Now neurons like to be excited,
that's why they have receptors.

00:18:05.339 --> 00:18:07.940
But they like to be tickled,
not bludgeoned.

00:18:07.940 --> 00:18:11.819
Chronic overstimulation of any neuron
anywhere in the body

00:18:11.819 --> 00:18:14.500
will lead to neuronal cell death.

00:18:14.500 --> 00:18:17.815
And we know this because kids who have
chronic long-term seizure disorders

00:18:17.816 --> 00:18:19.703
and status epilepticus

00:18:19.704 --> 00:18:22.460
have to be rushed to the ICU
and we have to stop their seizures.

00:18:22.460 --> 00:18:25.539
Because the longer the seizures go on,
the more brain damage occurs.

00:18:25.539 --> 00:18:27.779
So we notice.

00:18:27.779 --> 00:18:33.660
That second neuron that's receiving
the dopamine signal,

00:18:33.660 --> 00:18:37.539
it doesn't want to die,
it wants to protect itself.

00:18:37.539 --> 00:18:40.299
So it has a failsafe, it has a plan B.

00:18:40.299 --> 00:18:44.539
What it does is it down regulates
the number of receptors

00:18:44.539 --> 00:18:49.500
so that there is less chance, statistically,
through the law of mass action

00:18:49.500 --> 00:18:54.561
that any given molecule of dopamine
will find a receptor.

00:18:54.660 --> 00:18:55.863
It makes sense.

00:18:55.981 --> 00:18:59.019
Thereby reducing the game.

00:18:59.019 --> 00:19:01.500
So what does this mean in human terms?

00:19:01.500 --> 00:19:04.940
You get a hit, you get a rush,
receptors go down.

00:19:04.940 --> 00:19:09.099
Next time you need a bigger hit
to get the same rush, receptors go down,

00:19:09.099 --> 00:19:10.980
then a bigger hit, bigger hit.

00:19:10.980 --> 00:19:13.420
Until finally you need a huge hit
to get nothing.

00:19:13.420 --> 00:19:15.380
That's called tolerance.

00:19:15.380 --> 00:19:17.740
And then when the neurons
actually do start to die,

00:19:17.740 --> 00:19:19.689
that's called addiction.

00:19:19.690 --> 00:19:23.019
And guess what? When those neurons die,
they ain't coming back.

00:19:23.019 --> 00:19:25.619
Which is why addiction is so hard to treat.

